    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs exhibit distinct token biases (e.g., 'delve') and repetitive syntactic structures in creative writing due to RLHF alignment.",
        "Long-form synthetic fiction exposes context limitations, causing character amnesia, logical inconsistencies, and repetitive narrative loops during generation.",
        "These stylistic anomalies enable developers to train stylometric classifiers to detect machine-generated prose without explicit watermarking."
      ]
    },
